@* Lambda event handler (BENCH n°24): @onclick is an inline `() => count++` lambda, not a named
   method. The lambda body is translated (count -> count.value) through the same machinery @code
   methods use, so the click IS the measurement -- #count goes 0 -> 1 -> 2. *@

<p>Count: <span id="count">@count</span></p>

<button id="inc" @onclick="() => count++">Increment</button>

@code {
    private int count = 0;
}
